Version: 0.1.26
Date: 2026-04-16

Changes:
- Medium bench / bug-fix runtime improvements:
  - add a documented BugsInPy medium-bench writeup covering the validated
    `thefuck 1-8` case pool, baseline outcomes, failure-analysis correction,
    runtime changes, and rerun results.
  - strengthen bug-fix execution discipline in the system prompt and intent
    contract so failing tests/logs are treated as specification and source
    edits are preferred over broad exploratory drift.
  - add bug-fix convergence guardrails in the runtime loop to nudge the model
    toward the most likely implementation file when repeated tool batches do
    not produce file mutations.
  - extend medium-bench probe and analysis support, plus related tests and
    docs, to make real-case failure review reproducible.
- Validation:
  - rerun the validated BugsInPy `thefuck 1-8` buggy cases end-to-end and
    improve from `6/8` passing to `8/8` passing.
- REPL UX:
  - fix raw-mode slash submission so `/`, `/we`, and `/wechat` resolve to the
    unique `/wechat` command on Enter instead of staying as a no-op preview.

Related commits:
- feat(runtime): improve bug-fix convergence on medium bench
- fix(cli): resolve repl slash submit behavior
